cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing the memory abilities of RNNs in processing sequences of language. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes evaluation indicators to measure the memory abilities of different recurrent units, which is a common topic in machine learning research. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as RNNs are a popular type of AI model and the paper proposes a new approach to evaluate their memory abilities. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper focuses on analyzing the internal workings of RNNs, which are a type of neural network. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as RNNs are also used in image and video processing tasks, and the proposed evaluation indicators could be applied to evaluate their memory abilities in those domains as well.
